  <div class=3D"blog-body-1 blog-body-1--extended section">
    <div class=3D"blog-body__center container">
      <div class=3D"row">
        <div class=3D"blog-body-1__main col s9 md-s12">
          <div class=3D"blog-body-1__content"><h1 class=3D"blog-body-1__tit=
le"><span id=3D"hs_cos_wrapper_name" class=3D"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper=
_meta_field hs_cos_wrapper_type_text" style=3D"" data-hs-cos-general-type=
=3D"meta_field" data-hs-cos-type=3D"text">What is an association health pla=
n (AHP)?</span></h1><p class=3D"blog-body-1__info small-text">By <a href=3D=
"https://www.peoplekeep.com/blog/author/elizabeth-walker"><strong>Elizabeth=
 Walker</strong></a> on July 11, 2025 at 9:45 AM</p><span id=3D"hs_cos_wrap=
per_post_body" class=3D"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_meta_field hs_cos_wra=
pper_type_rich_text" style=3D"" data-hs-cos-general-type=3D"meta_field" dat=
a-hs-cos-type=3D"rich_text"><p>Offering a meaningful health benefit can be =
vital for small business owners to <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/bl=
og/which-benefits-have-the-best-effect-on-employee-retention-and-recruiting=
"><span>attract and retain</span></a> workers. But, offering a <a href=3D"h=
ttps://www.peoplekeep.com/blog/what-is-group-health-insurance"><span>tradit=
ional group health plan</span></a> can be difficult and expensive.</p>
<p>One affordable option is an association health plan (AHP). This type of =
health insurance is for businesses with a =E2=80=9Ccommonality of interest.=
=E2=80=9D But what does that mean for small employers looking to join an AH=
P?</p>
<p>Below, we=E2=80=99ll explore what AHPs mean for you and your employees a=
nd your alternative health insurance options as a small business owner.</p>
<p><!--more--></p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style=3D"color: #6dcdb8;"><strong>In this blog post, you=E2=80=99l=
l learn:</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level=3D"1">What AHPs are, including the potential cost savings an=
d risks for small businesses.</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">How AHPs compare to traditional group health insurance=
 plans.</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Alternative health benefit options, like health reimbu=
rsement arrangements (HRAs).</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>

<h2>What is an association health plan (AHP)?</h2>
<p>AHPs are health insurance arrangements for businesses with fewer than 50=
 employees and self-employed individuals. With an AHP, companies in the sam=
e industries and professions band together to buy <a href=3D"https://www.pe=
oplekeep.com/blog/small-group-vs.-large-group-health-insurance"><span>large=
 group</span></a> health plans or <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/blo=
g/fully-insured-vs-self-insured-health-plans"><span>self-insure</span></a>.=
 AHPs aren=E2=80=99t a new type of health insurance option. They=E2=80=99re=
 a way for small businesses to provide health coverage.</p>
<p>AHPs work like group health plans. But, they aren=E2=80=99t required to =
follow many <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/blog/what-is-the-affordab=
le-care-act-aca"><span>Affordable Care Act</span></a> (ACA) regulations. Fo=
r example, they don=E2=80=99t meet the <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.co=
m/blog/faq-ales-and-the-aca-employer-mandate"><span>employer mandate</span>=
</a> for <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/health-benefits/applicable-l=
arge-employers"><span>applicable large employers</span></a> (ALEs). They al=
so don=E2=80=99t have to cover the <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/bl=
og/what-are-the-10-essential-health-benefits"><span>ten essential health be=
nefits</span></a>, and can have limited plan options for employees.</p>
<p><strong>However, there are some advantages of AHPs:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level=3D"1">They can qualify as <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.=
com/blog/what-is-minimum-essential-coverage-mec"><span>minimum essential co=
verage</span></a> (MEC) under the Affordable Care Act.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li aria-level=3D"1">They=E2=80=99re compatible with <a href=3D"https://www=
.peoplekeep.com/health-savings-accounts"><span>health savings accounts</spa=
n></a> (HSAs) if your chosen group coverage is <a href=3D"https://www.peopl=
ekeep.com/blog/how-to-tell-if-your-hdhp-is-hsa-qualified"><span>HSA-qualifi=
ed</span></a>.</li>
</ul>
<p>You can design your AHP to best meet your staff=E2=80=99s health needs. =
For example, some AHPs offer less coverage for prescription drugs but great=
er coverage for annual wellness checkups with their primary care physician =
(PCP). So, it=E2=80=99s essential to understand what your employees are loo=
king for in a health benefit before you choose to offer an AHP.</p>
<p>However, not every business can create or join an association health pla=
n. Organizations with purposes or functions unrelated to offering benefits =
can create an AHP as part of their association. However, businesses can=E2=
=80=99t band together for the sole purpose of creating an AHP.</p>
<p>Additionally, each employer in the AHP must offer coverage to at least o=
ne common law employee who isn=E2=80=99t a spouse of the employer<sup>1</su=
p>.</p>
<h2>How much do employers save with an AHP?</h2>
<p>AHP representatives negotiate with health insurance companies, medical n=
etwork providers, and other suppliers for lower <a href=3D"https://www.peop=
lekeep.com/blog/how-are-health-insurance-premiums-calculated"><span>premium=
 rates</span></a> and more affordable healthcare services. Depending on how=
 you design your plan, employers may save 10% to 30% on average on AHP prem=
iums compared to traditional group health plans.</p>
<p>These savings could be because many AHPs don=E2=80=99t need to cover ess=
ential health benefits. This puts workers at risk of not having coverage fo=
r prescription drugs, maternity care, mental health services, and more.</p>
<p>Although lower in cost, AHPs have fewer consumer protections. AHP critic=
s claim the plan encourages healthy workers to leave the individual market.=
 This can make the market less competitive and leave behind sicker employee=
s who are more costly to insure.</p>
<h2>How do AHPs differ from group health insurance?</h2>
<p>The biggest difference between AHPs and group health plans is that AHPs =
aren=E2=80=99t subject to many ACA regulations that other insurance compani=
es must follow.</p>
<p><strong>For example, AHPs can charge members higher premiums depending o=
n:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Age</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Current health conditions</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Gender</li>
</ul>
<p>Additionally, unlike large group plans, they can=E2=80=99t refuse to cov=
er treatment associated with a pre-existing condition.</p>
<p>Although both insurance options have been around for years, AHPs have a =
history of financial instability and leaving members unexpectedly uninsured=
. They can offer significant savings for employers. But you should carefull=
y consider if they=E2=80=99re the right choice for your employees.</p>
<h2>How can employers enroll in an AHP?</h2>
<p>Like traditional group plans, employers can enroll in an AHP during the =
plan=E2=80=99s annual enrollment period. Membership criteria vary by associ=
ation. But typically, you must provide certain business information to enro=
ll.</p>
<p><strong>This includes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Your business type (i.e., for-profit, non-profit, inco=
rporated, etc.)</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Your business taxes from the previous year</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Your company=E2=80=99s location</li>
</ul>
<p>To get a more accurate estimated rate, you must know the number of emplo=
yees you=E2=80=99re offering the AHP, their ages, and their eligible depend=
ents. But even if you offer your employees coverage, they can decline to jo=
in.</p>
<p>Once they enroll, your employees will receive an insurance card, like th=
ey would with other employer-sponsored group plans.</p>
<h2>What are alternative health benefit options for small employers?</h2>
<p>While they can be financially beneficial, AHPs don=E2=80=99t always prov=
ide the most comprehensive coverage for employees in the long run. If you=
=E2=80=99re seeking an escape from traditional group health plans, consider=
 offering a stand-alone <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/health-reimbu=
rsement-arrangement-hra"><span>health reimbursement arrangement</span></a> =
(HRA).</p>
<p>A stand-alone HRA is a <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/blog/is-hea=
lth-insurance-reimbursement-taxable"><span>tax-advantaged</span></a> health=
 benefit that enables employers to reimburse employees for <a href=3D"https=
://www.peoplekeep.com/hra-eligible-expenses"><span>qualified</span></a> out=
-of-pocket medical care expenses like individual health insurance premiums.=
</p>
<p><strong>Here=E2=80=99s how an HRA works in three easy steps:</strong></p=
>
<ol>
<li aria-level=3D"1">You choose a monthly amount of tax-free money that emp=
loyees can spend on out-of-pocket medical care and individual health insura=
nce policies. Your staff can buy qualified health plans through a <a href=
=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/blog/public-vs-private-health-insurance-exch=
anges"><span>public or private exchange</span></a> and get their essential =
benefits covered under the ACA.</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Then, employees buy healthcare items and services and =
<a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/blog/hra-claim-documentation-requirem=
ents"><span>submit proof</span></a> to you of an eligible purchase. IRS Pub=
lication 502<sup>2</sup> and the CARES Act<sup>3</sup> outline the expenses=
 employees can buy with their HRA funds. Employers can limit reimbursements=
 to premiums only if they choose.</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Once you review an employee=E2=80=99s claim, you reimb=
urse them tax-free up to their allowance amount. Unspent HRA funds stay wit=
h you at the end of the plan year or if a worker leaves your company.</li>
</ol>
<p>In the sections below, we=E2=80=99ll examine two popular types of <a hre=
f=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/blog/pros-and-cons-of-stand-alone-hras"><sp=
an>stand-alone HRAs</span></a>.</p>
<h3><span style=3D"font-size: 14px; color: #000000;">Qualified small employ=
er HRA (QSEHRA)</span></h3>
<p>First, let=E2=80=99s look at the <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/q=
ualified-small-employer-hra-qsehra"><span>QSEHRA</span></a>. With this type=
 of HRA, employers with fewer than 50 <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com=
/blog/fte-calculation"><span>full-time equivalent employees</span></a> (FTE=
s) can reimburse their staff for medical costs and individual coverage. To =
offer this benefit, you need at least one W-2 worker. This makes the QSEHRA=
 ideal for employers looking for options other than self-funded policies, s=
mall group plans, or AHPs.</p>
<p><strong>Here=E2=80=99s how the QSEHRA works:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level=3D"1">The QSEHRA has no minimum contribution limits, but the=
 IRS does set <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/blog/qsehra-contributio=
n-limits" rel=3D"noopener"><span>maximum contribution limits</span></a>. Ad=
ditionally, you have the flexibility to customize monthly allowances by fam=
ily status or age.</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">By law, you must offer all your full-time W-2 employee=
s the QSEHRA. You can also allow part-time staff members to use the benefit=
 as long as they receive the same allowance as your full-time workers. Addi=
tionally, <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/blog/hra-eligibility-by-typ=
e-of-small-business-owner"><span>certain types</span></a> of business owner=
s are eligible to join.</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">If you want to save money, you can design the benefit =
to reimburse employees only for their health insurance premiums.</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Employees must have a health plan that provides MEC to=
 participate in the benefit. MEC includes <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep=
.com/blog/which-health-plans-are-aca-compliant"><span>ACA-compliant policie=
s</span></a> on the individual health insurance market, Medicare, Medicaid,=
 and <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/blog/what-is-a-catastrophic-heal=
th-insurance-plan"><span>catastrophic plans</span></a>. Employees with cove=
rage through a parent=E2=80=99s or spouse=E2=80=99s group plan can also par=
ticipate.</li>
</ul>
<h3><span style=3D"font-size: 14px; color: #000000;">Individual coverage HR=
A (ICHRA)</span></h3>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/individual-coverage-hra-ichra"=
><span>ICHRA</span></a> is a popular alternative to traditional group healt=
h plans for employers of any size. Like the QSEHRA, it can help your employ=
ees pay for their individual health insurance premiums and other qualified =
medical costs. But it has some key differences from the QSEHRA.</p>
<p><strong>Here are a few ways the ICHRA differs:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level=3D"1">The ICHRA has no maximum allowance requirements. This =
flexibility can make it an excellent choice for organizations with growing =
staff sizes or those looking to attract more quality workers.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li aria-level=3D"1">You can set different eligibility requirements and all=
owance amounts by <a href=3D"https://www.peoplekeep.com/blog/individual-cov=
erage-hra-ichra-employee-classes"><span>employee classes</span></a>, age, o=
r family size, giving you greater control over your budget and plan design.=
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Employees must have a qualifying form of individual he=
alth insurance to use the benefit.</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Large employers can leverage the ICHRA to satisfy the =
employer mandate. As long as the ICHRA allowance is <a href=3D"https://www.=
peoplekeep.com/blog/determining-ichra-affordability"><span>affordable</span=
></a>, ALEs can avoid buying group coverage while complying with ACA requir=
ements.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Conclusion</h2>
<p>AHPs can be a great cost-saving way to offer health benefits to employee=
s. But with low regulations and high risk, many employers don=E2=80=99t see=
 them as valuable perks. Luckily, other affordable options, such as HRAs, a=
re budget-friendly and provide your employees with comprehensive health cov=
erage.</p>
<p>HRAs allow employees to buy their own health insurance, helping you avoi=
d many pitfalls of AHPs. If you=E2=80=99re interested in an HRA for your bu=
siness, PeopleKeep by Remodel Health can get you started. <a href=3D"https:=
//www.peoplekeep.com/contact-sales"><span>Schedule a call</span></a> with a=
n HRA specialist, and we=E2=80=99ll help you design your benefit.</p>
